result.execSummary:
The defendant C'era Chanell Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant C'era C Jones in court, in custody.  Attorney John Mathew Krejci in court for C'era C Jones.  Prosecuting attorney Katrina Voge in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Pursuant to negotiations, court orders counts one and three dismissed but read in. 
AS TO COUNT ONE TWO; Defendant changes pleas to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's pleas.  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    
AS TO COUNT TWO; Defendant ordered to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, concurrent with any other sentence, credit of 86 days time served. THIS IS A TIME SERVIED DISPOSITION. 

- Submit a DNA sample by the surcharge by March 15th, 2024.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment/tax intercept

- Pay all MANDATORY costs, fees and surcharges by March 15th, 2024. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment/tax intercept.
- Defendant advised of his right to appeal.

Attorney John Mathew Krejci in court, defendant C'era C Jones not in court, in custody, appearance waived.  Katrina Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court. Attorney Krejci is waiting on an offer. Case is adjourned in Branch 01.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Attorney John Mathew Krejci in court, defendant C'era C Jones not in court, in custody.
